result.adr_address: 37 Mosque St, Mid-Levels, Hong Kong
result.name: Xoco Mexican Restaurant

reviews.text: Amazing Margaritas, the standard are good but ask for their specials if you want to be pleasantly surprised. The food is authentic - we enjoyed their Tacos and Fajitas. Portions are huge compared to other Mexican restaurants in Asia.
Tasty, authentic Mexican and good service. No pretentiousness.
Probably the best Mexican food in HK. Pretty comparable to the Bay Area Mexican restaurants, although the price is on the high side, even by California standards. Overall a pleasant experience.

Coming from San Diego. I can tell you this is pretty good Mexican food as far as Asia goes. Went here with a group of 10 Americans, they were able to accommodate us nicely. Got 3 pitchers of margaritas for the table. Good quality drinks. Overall a good spot for American Express card Patriots who are looking for Mexican food while traveling or on. Business in Hong Kong
delicious food and.big portion good service
